name: Alpha Players
directions: Enter in the front, the right door leads to the main store and there is a restroom in the back. (If you enter in the back, this is immediately to your right.) If occupied, there is another one if you take the left door after the main entrance (if locked, ask a worker in the main store to let you in). Once you're in that room, head towards the back near the concession stand; there is one genderneutral bathroom and one single-stall "men's room" there.

comment: You *might* have to buy something but I've never had to since I've only been there to play at hosted events. If they make you, they sell snacks and sodas for $1.

name: Kalamazoo College
directions: ARCUS CENTER: This building has multiple single-stall genderneutral and handicap accessible restrooms, all on the upper levels of the building ("first floor"). FITNESS AND WELLNESS CENTER: Go past the front desk to the right, there is a genderneutral and handicap accessible restroom with a small shower. LIBRARY: 1st floor, behind the large gray stairs you see from the entrance. The bathroom has 2 stalls but is still genderneutral and handicap accessible. It used to be a "mens room" and the "womens room" is right next to it meaning most people treat it as a men's room so keep that in mind. No student ID needed. LIGHT FINE ARTS BUILDING: 2nd floor, west side of building. An elevator (or stairs) on the 1st floor towards the east side can help you get there. Student ID needed at evening hours. MANDELLE HALL: Go straight past the stairs after entering in the front. No student ID needed. Genderneutral and handicap accessible. HUMPHREY HOUSE: Look right immediately when you enter in the main entrance. Genderneutral and handicap accessible. HICKS CENTER: 2nd floor, next to the Richardson Room (AKA: "Stacks"). Both have 2 stalls but are still genderneutral and handicap accessible. No student ID needed throughout the active school year. DEWATERS HALL: There is a genderneutral bathroom on every floor of this building down the halls of the dorm rooms. The residence hall has no elevators but the bathrooms themselves are accessible. Student ID needed to enter building. Crissey, Trowbridge and Severn have at least one all-gender restroom; but idk where those are and these halls also have no elevator and need a Student ID to enter building.
comment: This is a relatively small campus with multiple gendernuetral and handicap accessable restrooms (although the hilly terrain will make it tough for PWDs to navigate), most buildings on campus have at least one of each.

name: Saugatuck Dunes State Park
comment: In the state park, you may need a state park pass to get in, though I have never seen the checking booth staffed. Single person unisex outhouses, up a small rise from one of the parking lots (don't recall which, sorry), as well as in the park. Marked inaccessible because I don't remember if the ones by the parking lot are and the rest are on hiking trails.
